A trio of men in tight harmony sang the national anthem and other classic patriotic songs. With the exception of the anthem, most attendees remained seated and did not sing along until one particular country song began. I'll bet you can guess which one. The one by Lee Greenwood. Suddenly people were singing along, and when the words "stand up" were sung, fully 2/3 of the audience stood up together and kept singing along. I wonder where they learned to do that? My wife began quietly crying.  An exception was a Marine vet in front of us, who had stood ramrod straight earlier when the Marine Corps Hymn was played by the band. This time, he and his wife and child remained seated, a small measure of comfort for we who do not share the values of our current "leaders." That is one country song that if I never hear again, I will be grateful.

